    <script type="text/javascript">
        $(document).ready(function() {
            $('.select .select-container div:nth-child(' + ($('.tab.current', '#section6').index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').hide();
            
            $('.tab', '#section6').click(function() {
                $('.tab, .tab-content', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $(this).addClass('current');
                $('.tab-content[data-id=' + $(this).data('id') + ']', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div:nth-child(' + ($(this).index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').addClass('current');
                chkContentHeight();
            });

            $('.tab-select', '#section6').change(function() {
                $('.tab, .tab-content', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $('.tab[data-id=' + $(this).val() + ']', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.tab-content[data-id=' + $(this).val() + ']', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div:nth-child(' +  ($('.tab.current', '#section6').index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.select .select-container div', '#section6').show();
                $('.select .select-container div:nth-child(' + ($('.tab.current', '#section6').index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').hide();
                chkContentHeight();
            });

            $('.record-slider', '#section6').Slider({
                slides: '.record-item',
                maxSlide: 1,
                swipeControl: true,
                skipBoundary: true,
                infiniteLoop: true
            });

            function chkContentHeight() {
                $('p.description', '#section6').each(function() {
                    if($(this).height() > 160) {
                        $(this).parent().addClass('more');
                    }
                });
            }
            chkContentHeight();

            $('.record-item article button.view-more', '#section6').click(function() {
                $(this).hide();
                $(this).parent().find('.view-less').show();
                $(this).parent().find('.description').hide();
                $(this).parent().find('.content').show();
            });
            $('.record-item article button.view-less', '#section6').click(function() {
                $(this).hide();
                $(this).parent().find('.view-more').show();
                $(this).parent().find('.description').show();
                $(this).parent().find('.content').hide();
            });
        });
    </script>
</section>
<section id="section7" data-total="10">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
            <h2 class="colour2">What's new at KGV?</h2>
            <span class="bg-colour1"></span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="record-slider">
        <div class="slider-container">
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="266">
                        <time>25/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>As our ESF Artist in Residence, SuRie recently graced the KGV stage for a concert, filling the hall with her soulful voice. It was an absolute treat for our community!<br><br>SuRie is a singer-songwriter, actor, and musician from London.<br><br>Beyond the concert, SuRie spent time working directly with ESF students, hosting hands-on workshops focused on songwriting and music composition.<br><br>A massive thank you to SuRie for sharing her talent and knowledge with us!<br><br>#SuRie #ESFArtistInResidence #ESFSchool #kgv_hk #studentmusicians</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/721a093cbfa5bdfa19f2d963d954cabd.jpg" alt="657091740_1522084303257872_5866826132559144637_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="265">
                        <time>20/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>For International Women’s Month, KGV’s 'Girl Talk' brought a Period Cramp Simulator to campus! It was a hilarious, eye-opening way to break the stigma and build a little empathy for what women power through every single month.<br><br>Huge shoutout to Girl Talk and all the brave volunteers who stepped up to the challenge!<br><br>#InternationalWomensMonth #kgv_hk #ESFSchools</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/5b32bea34a8388551bdded85366b4a43.jpg" alt="655608469_18453942526108639_6557197794566346300_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="264">
                        <time>20/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>We are so proud of our student speakers who took the stage to share their powerful ideas and inspiring stories. Beyond the thought-provoking talks, it was wonderful to see our community connect over light refreshments and great networking between guests, alumni, and students.<br><br>We also got to hear some of our alumni speak about their the paths they took to become who they are today!<br><br>A special shoutout goes to the organisers of the event and a big thank you to everyone who joined us to make it a memorable event!<br><br>#TEDxKGVSchoolYouth #StudentVoices #KGVCommunity #kgv_hk #esfschools</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/00b01e8ed31e20f948bdb50373522ca2.jpg" alt="653716220_1517086693757633_5075464912459752569_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="263">
                        <time>18/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Ritu Hemnani, the award winning author of Lion of the Sky returned to King George V to share her story-telling expertise with Y7 and 8. The Year 7s took acting to the next level and the Year 8s learnt just how powerful words can be, they could even save a life! <br> <br>Thank you to the English department and the Library for organizing this event!<br>#kgv_hk #ESFSchools #english #storytelling #guestspeaker</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/8aa906262c2fc9dc723473029a6302de.jpg" alt="654612026_1515305170602452_1021374612367933891_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="262">
                        <time>13/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Our Year 12 Business and Economics students competed at the ESF Marketing Competition. We are incredibly proud of their efforts in creating marketing campaigns under intense time pressure!<br><br>KMB’s Winning Pick (Team 2): Justin, Prisha, Daniel, Duncan, Uriel, and Hannah.<br>Overall Runner-up (Team 1): Rakin, Praneel, Coco, Gwyneth, Renee, and Zarra.<br><br>Seeing such creativity in action was truly remarkable. Huge congratulations to both teams!<br>#ESFShools #kgv_hk #businessstudents #econstudents #studentbusinessideas</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/b4eacf055a90f467d577cca8b14f0f6c.jpg" alt="649645886_1509888711144098_585160248197596481_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="261">
                        <time>12/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>A group of KGV parents, staff, and students recently participated in a forest restoration walk in Mui Wo. This featured walk was donated as part of the silent auction for the 130th Anniversary Gala in September 2025. <br><br>Passionate about forest restoration, Paul Melsom, who is an extremely  accomplished horticulturist has been working on the forest landscape restoration project for decades.<br><br> Paul’s crucial work focuses on ecological restoration areas ravaged by hill fires, planting native trees to restore and sustain the local ecosystem.<br><br>The walk offered a wonderful opportunity to see the successful growth of some of the 250 native tree species which are now established and the recently planted promising young saplings that will add more biodiversity for the future forest.<br><br>Over 2O years, along with many other schools and volunteers,  KGV School students have contributed greatly to this project through growing some tree seedlings in the School, planting the tree seedlings and maintaining them on the Lantau project.<br><br>Projects like this benefit immensely from the dedication of knowledgeable and passionate individuals like Paul, who often self-funds the cost and also some succour from Kadoorie Farm and Botanic Garden. Its impact is immeasurable, and its legacy needs more ongoing community support. If you are interested in helping, please contact office@kgv.edu.hk <br><br>Paul provides landscape consultation service to school and runs the gardening club on Thursdays.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/b8d89a4efa1fda8ba2268e2da92c5579.jpg" alt="650343114_1509199387879697_8503653010055902517_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="260">
                        <time>11/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Our students have been showing what it means to be truly remarkable. Congratulations to our athletes for their success in the latest HKSSF competitions!<br><br>Cross-Country (Division 1)<br><br>Kyle: 1st Place (Boys C Grade)<br><br>Jacob: 2nd Place (Boys C Grade)<br><br>Boys U14 Team: 2nd Overall<br><br>Team Standings: Girls 5th Overall | Boys 7th Overall<br><br>Fencing (Sabre)<br><br>Belva Cheung: 🥇 1st Place (Girls B Grade)<br><br>Eunis Tsui: 🥉 3rd Place (Girls C Grade)<br><br>Well done to all competitors! Good luck to our fencers as they head into the team championships in two weeks.<br><br>#KGVSports #ESFSchools #kgv_hk #studentathletes</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/01b6d6d736a6fa8d9666c52649aebb14.jpg" alt="649476591_1508274204638882_8744114434905521610_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="259">
                        <time>10/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>We are proud to see our students striving to "Be Your Own Remarkable" in everything they do. Join us in celebrating these recent achievements:<br><br>Anvi: Represented Hong Kong to win 1st Place in a global Marathi singing contest, following months of dedicated practice.<br><br>Austin: Secured 2nd Place in the Kowloon City District All Hong Kong Inter-school Fencing Invitational.<br><br>Ella: Made her public performance debut in musical theatre at both the HK Arts Centre and the AIA Carnival.<br><br>#studentspotlights #kgv_hk #ESFSchools</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/a94a2847bf9f0b84c12c10af800a375d.jpg" alt="650218081_1508103844655918_4556422647107286229_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="258">
                        <time>05/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>A huge congratulation to year 12 Film and Drama students Rachell Lee, Jayne Lau and Sonakshi Shrivastava for having their short film ‘As You Wish’ selected for the Audience Choice Awards in both Babel Film Festival HK and the PKX Teen Arts & Film Festival set in New York.<br><br>The Film department are incredibly proud of their hard work and creativity in their dedication to create meaningful visual storytelling.  #esfschools #kgv_hk #filmstudents #media #film</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/ce8abd29c5054868a1a72b4f5bfc8ac0.jpg" alt="646150340_1503908675075435_5043102204561790041_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="257">
                        <time>27/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>The KGV stage is still cooling down! Last week, 10 student bands performed for an unforgettable night of talent and high energy. <br><br>A massive shout-out to every musician who performed—you guys made it a night to remember! Thank you to the guests for making the atmosphere electric. <br><br>Photo Credits: Huge thanks to student photographer Stephen and Ms. Carlile for capturing these epic moments!<br><br>#kgv_hk #esfschools #studentmusicians #lionrock #battleofthebands #LiveMusic</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/813df42d3801a4308bc4ff9745c4cc8b.jpg" alt="643412954_1498478428951793_5439065282363201229_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="266">
                        <time>25/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>As our ESF Artist in Residence, SuRie recently graced the KGV stage for a concert, filling the hall with her soulful voice. It was an absolute treat for our community!<br><br>SuRie is a singer-songwriter, actor, and musician from London.<br><br>Beyond the concert, SuRie spent time working directly with ESF students, hosting hands-on workshops focused on songwriting and music composition.<br><br>A massive thank you to SuRie for sharing her talent and knowledge with us!<br><br>#SuRie #ESFArtistInResidence #ESFSchool #kgv_hk #studentmusicians</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/721a093cbfa5bdfa19f2d963d954cabd.jpg" alt="657091740_1522084303257872_5866826132559144637_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="265">
                        <time>20/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>For International Women’s Month, KGV’s 'Girl Talk' brought a Period Cramp Simulator to campus! It was a hilarious, eye-opening way to break the stigma and build a little empathy for what women power through every single month.<br><br>Huge shoutout to Girl Talk and all the brave volunteers who stepped up to the challenge!<br><br>#InternationalWomensMonth #kgv_hk #ESFSchools</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/5b32bea34a8388551bdded85366b4a43.jpg" alt="655608469_18453942526108639_6557197794566346300_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="264">
                        <time>20/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>We are so proud of our student speakers who took the stage to share their powerful ideas and inspiring stories. Beyond the thought-provoking talks, it was wonderful to see our community connect over light refreshments and great networking between guests, alumni, and students.<br><br>We also got to hear some of our alumni speak about their the paths they took to become who they are today!<br><br>A special shoutout goes to the organisers of the event and a big thank you to everyone who joined us to make it a memorable event!<br><br>#TEDxKGVSchoolYouth #StudentVoices #KGVCommunity #kgv_hk #esfschools</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/00b01e8ed31e20f948bdb50373522ca2.jpg" alt="653716220_1517086693757633_5075464912459752569_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="263">
                        <time>18/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Ritu Hemnani, the award winning author of Lion of the Sky returned to King George V to share her story-telling expertise with Y7 and 8. The Year 7s took acting to the next level and the Year 8s learnt just how powerful words can be, they could even save a life! <br> <br>Thank you to the English department and the Library for organizing this event!<br>#kgv_hk #ESFSchools #english #storytelling #guestspeaker</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/8aa906262c2fc9dc723473029a6302de.jpg" alt="654612026_1515305170602452_1021374612367933891_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="262">
                        <time>13/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Our Year 12 Business and Economics students competed at the ESF Marketing Competition. We are incredibly proud of their efforts in creating marketing campaigns under intense time pressure!<br><br>KMB’s Winning Pick (Team 2): Justin, Prisha, Daniel, Duncan, Uriel, and Hannah.<br>Overall Runner-up (Team 1): Rakin, Praneel, Coco, Gwyneth, Renee, and Zarra.<br><br>Seeing such creativity in action was truly remarkable. Huge congratulations to both teams!<br>#ESFShools #kgv_hk #businessstudents #econstudents #studentbusinessideas</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/b4eacf055a90f467d577cca8b14f0f6c.jpg" alt="649645886_1509888711144098_585160248197596481_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="261">
                        <time>12/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>A group of KGV parents, staff, and students recently participated in a forest restoration walk in Mui Wo. This featured walk was donated as part of the silent auction for the 130th Anniversary Gala in September 2025. <br><br>Passionate about forest restoration, Paul Melsom, who is an extremely  accomplished horticulturist has been working on the forest landscape restoration project for decades.<br><br> Paul’s crucial work focuses on ecological restoration areas ravaged by hill fires, planting native trees to restore and sustain the local ecosystem.<br><br>The walk offered a wonderful opportunity to see the successful growth of some of the 250 native tree species which are now established and the recently planted promising young saplings that will add more biodiversity for the future forest.<br><br>Over 2O years, along with many other schools and volunteers,  KGV School students have contributed greatly to this project through growing some tree seedlings in the School, planting the tree seedlings and maintaining them on the Lantau project.<br><br>Projects like this benefit immensely from the dedication of knowledgeable and passionate individuals like Paul, who often self-funds the cost and also some succour from Kadoorie Farm and Botanic Garden. Its impact is immeasurable, and its legacy needs more ongoing community support. If you are interested in helping, please contact office@kgv.edu.hk <br><br>Paul provides landscape consultation service to school and runs the gardening club on Thursdays.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/b8d89a4efa1fda8ba2268e2da92c5579.jpg" alt="650343114_1509199387879697_8503653010055902517_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="260">
                        <time>11/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Our students have been showing what it means to be truly remarkable. Congratulations to our athletes for their success in the latest HKSSF competitions!<br><br>Cross-Country (Division 1)<br><br>Kyle: 1st Place (Boys C Grade)<br><br>Jacob: 2nd Place (Boys C Grade)<br><br>Boys U14 Team: 2nd Overall<br><br>Team Standings: Girls 5th Overall | Boys 7th Overall<br><br>Fencing (Sabre)<br><br>Belva Cheung: 🥇 1st Place (Girls B Grade)<br><br>Eunis Tsui: 🥉 3rd Place (Girls C Grade)<br><br>Well done to all competitors! Good luck to our fencers as they head into the team championships in two weeks.<br><br>#KGVSports #ESFSchools #kgv_hk #studentathletes</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/01b6d6d736a6fa8d9666c52649aebb14.jpg" alt="649476591_1508274204638882_8744114434905521610_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="259">
                        <time>10/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>We are proud to see our students striving to "Be Your Own Remarkable" in everything they do. Join us in celebrating these recent achievements:<br><br>Anvi: Represented Hong Kong to win 1st Place in a global Marathi singing contest, following months of dedicated practice.<br><br>Austin: Secured 2nd Place in the Kowloon City District All Hong Kong Inter-school Fencing Invitational.<br><br>Ella: Made her public performance debut in musical theatre at both the HK Arts Centre and the AIA Carnival.<br><br>#studentspotlights #kgv_hk #ESFSchools</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/a94a2847bf9f0b84c12c10af800a375d.jpg" alt="650218081_1508103844655918_4556422647107286229_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
